Matthias Goerne (baritone), Alexander Schmalcz (piano). Rating: * * * * By Rupert Christiansen
6:42PM GMT 18 Feb 2011
Comments
Harmonia Mundi HMC 902063, £13.99
This is a selection of Schubert’s lieder, sung by Matthias Goerne with exquisite artistry. Only the warmth and simplicity that Goerne’s contemporary Christian Gerhaher brings to this music are lacking: as in his mannered interpretation of the title song, Goerne some-times allows the line to lose buoyancy and introspection to become affectation.
