Go Ape swings for more expansion
Treetop assault course provider Go Ape is to create 100 new jobs as it opens a new site in southern England. Go Ape is set to open its 29th forest adventure playground this year By Denise Roland
4:25PM GMT 04 Feb 2013
Comments
The forest adventure company, which saw visitor numbers hit a record high in excess of half a million in 2012, will embark on a plan to boost revenue by 20pc as it opens its 29th location, in Tilgate Country Park, West Sussex. Go Ape also plans to add new courses to some of its existing sites in England, Scotland and Wales, and double its US presence to six locations. "2013 marks the next phase in an exciting new chapter for Go Ape,” said Jerome Mayhew, managing director at Go Ape. “Last year saw us embark on ambitious growth plans following a rapid rise in consumer demand for outdoor-based activities. It resulted in our best year to date."
The company, established in 2001 by husband-and-wife team Tristram and Rebecca Mayhew, has won a raft of business awards for its high-wire forest adventure playgrounds and said turnover hit £12m in 2012.
